<br>
Back before anyone tried to go to the moon, ppl were speculating that the thing was made outta cheese (why?  I haven't the slightest clue).  And as everyone knows the myth behind rats and mice liking cheese.  I  figure they might make them the new race.  As well one thing that would support this idea is look at all the rats out there. <p>Liddlerunt Wyldefeather 37th season Druid





</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/usomberlainwayfaerer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Somberlain Wayfaerer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(4/19/01 10:14:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shadows of Luclin... EQ2? Release 12/03/01</span><hr size=1> Well, according to an interview with Jeff Butler (link on Casters Realm), it will be Kerrans for the new race and Beastmaster as the new class.  There were no further details, except that there will be on additional starting city.  Kerra Ridge certainly would be a decent starting city, as it is big enough and has a lot of un(der)utilized NPCs who could become guild trainers and give quests.  Just a thought.  Not as if the zone sees any use now.  With Stonebrunt Mountains getting added this summer, I'm sure they'll add content that will provide background for the addition of Kerrans later in the year.<br>
<br>
My only concern is that, based on the interview and three screenshots provided, it will have steeper hardware requirements.  I realize that &quot;progress&quot; means raising the bar on hardware performance, but if they really mean to compete with the next batch of RPGs (and if the screenshots are an accurate preview), one of my two PCs won't be able to handle the graphics.  Oh well, I guess that just means no expansion on that one.  Whose bright idea was onboard video anyway?<br>
<br>
<br>
